fields.details:
Megan Thompson is a Montana native now living and working in Los Angeles, California.

She graduated from Montana State University in 2008 with a degree in photography.

Her work has been published in Rolling Stone, Alternative Press, Substream, Rock Sound, Kerrang, among others, and she has received recognition from Photo District News, and Photo Lucida’s Critical Mass competition for her fine art work.


Megan is a dog person and available for creative assignment worldwide!

fields.description: 50 First Jokes is an event in which 50 comedians tell their first joke of the year. I was asked to photograph the 2015 Los Angeles event which was held at the historic Roosevelt Hotel in Hollywood, and took these portraits as each comedian finished their joke.
fields.title: 50 First Jokes

fields.description: On the first & third Tuesday of every month, Loud Village hosts a comedy show inside of a Los Feliz fish taco stand. What started as a small show has grown into one of the top comedy events in the city. The crowded outdoor stage has hosted small local acts just getting their start, & celebrities like Aziz Ansari, Michael Che, Nick Kroll, & Paul Scheer. Several comics have gone on to bigger things like Saturday Night Live, & Comedy Central. For the past three years I've been out on the street photographing each comic as they come off stage.
